The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 24 February is 224,454 (25,869.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 19 February, there were 6,093 new confirmed cases (702.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 12 February, there were 7,708 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 21% (1,615 fewer cases).
